There’s a Moth in my Soup!
The worst part about seasons changing in Denver? The insect migration. Specifically, moths. Moths are the bane of my existence. The most obnoxious of moths were migrating to Denver one year, and it was the most annoying thing I have ever experienced in my entire san-jū nana years of LIFE. Every day for two-three weeks these Jackson moths would fly everywhere and anywhere in all things at once. All throughout the day moths are flying around something, stuck on something, dead in something. Just utter spring-time mother nature foolery; trolling Colorado on top of the crazy wildfires and bipolar weather one could have ever seen. I found a moth, one month later, behind my dresser, as stiff as my drink. NEXT!